                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751.67/249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-19T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 19, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 19—3:41 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Supplementing my telegram No. 14, April 11, 10 a.m. from Istanbul. Although I
                    am still unable to obtain confirmation, I have reason to believe that Turkey has
                    decided to hold in abeyance the question of annexation of the Hatay, primarily
                    in order to avoid the appearance of aggressiveness at this juncture.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
